<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-281-801  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 281 801.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  Jan 1989 v21 n1 p24(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dental equipment maker uses microcomputer-based data managementand production planning system.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Randhawa, Sabah U.; McDowell, Edward D.; Pendakur, Ramesh; Cook,Charles N.; Welch, Thomas A.; Gaibler, Cheryl.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A microcomputer-based data management and production planningsystem was developed for and is being implemented in Newberg, ORdental equipment maker A-dec Inc's Dental Furniture Operations(DFO).andP;  The system is design to manage the extensive parts,assembly, and manpower planning, and production schedulingrequired because 60-75 percent of DFO manufacturing production isin small quantities and 25-40 percent is in extremely smallquantities for custom orders.andP;  Main components of the system are adatabase management module, which maintains sales order andproduct structure information, and a scheduling and interactiveload balancing module, which generates production schedules,predicts required production capacities, and modifies productionschedules according to system constraints.andP;  The system isimplemented in dBase III Plus and works on an IBM PC-XT orcompatible.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   A-Dec Inc. (production control).andO;Topic:     System DevelopmentCase StudyData ManagementDentistryComputer-Integrated ManufacturingSpecificationsRelational DBMSMicrocomputers.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttablegraph.andO;Caption:   System's two main components. (chart)A-dec product structure report. (table)Assembly schedules before and after balancing attempt. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>